Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents an algorithmic and complexity analysis of a method for real root isolation of polynomials, which involves numerical computations.
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper deals with polynomial computations and presents an implementation in a symbolic computation library (\synaps).
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents algorithmic and complexity results for real root isolation of polynomials, which involves data structures and algorithms.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with the computation of real roots of polynomials, which can be seen as a problem in computational geometry.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the extension of the algorithm to non square-free polynomials, which can be relevant in control theory and system identification.
